A further EUR 400 million for infrastructure
Finance Minister János Veres and Marta Gajecka, Vice-President of the European Investment Bank (EIB), signed three loan agreements in Budapest on Friday, with a total value of EUR 400 million.
In 2006, the European Investment Bank (EIB) approved a EUR 300 million framework for the financing of transport and environmental projects implemented with grants from the Cohesion Fund.The EUR 100 million loan agreement has already been signed earlier, the current agreement is about the use of the EUR 200 million loaned.
The sum of EUR 150 million agreed in the loan agreement will also be spent on the budgetary financing of educational projects.
