The driving licence was a document in which everyone could decide whether or not to own it.
It was not an identity card that everyone, and indeed a valid one, had to have.
People who don't want to drive should give up their driver's license.
It is enough to take him to the competent municipal office or send him there by registered letter.
At the end of the year, driving licences issued between 1964 and 1993 will become invalid.
However, drivers will gradually have to exchange other types of driving licences.
