On Wednesday, at the last meeting of the negotiations in Vienna, no agreement was reached on the future status of the province.
At the end of the failure
The Serbs and Albanians from Kosovo closed a sixth and final discussion session in Baden, Austria, Wednesday morning, without overcoming their controversy over the future status of the separatist province.
