Emphasizing that peace in the region is at stake, its American counterpart, Frank Wilsner, called on Belgrade and Pristina to fulfil their commitments to maintain peace and to continue the talks beyond the end of the negotiations.
No violence is expected in the immediate future, but we are at the beginning of a very difficult time, he added, indicating that there are quite clear tensions.
End of placements on 10 December
The mediators of the Troika, which unites the European Union, the US and Russia, will meet for the last time in Serbia and Kosovo on Monday.
