The talks held by Baden, near Vienna, formed the sixth and final negotiating meeting since the Troika had been given a mandate by the UN last August for a new mediation.
Americans and Europeans expect their mediation mission to end on 10 December.
The Russians, who had already blocked the granting of Kosovo's independence to the Security Council, insist on continuing negotiations beyond this end date.
Russia was and remains the advocate of a negotiated solution, a mutually agreed solution, said Botsane-Khartchenko.
