Which insurance is best for me?
Car insurance, which covers a possible case of damage caused by the driver, involves a high cost, the amount of which again depends on various factors, including age, gender, the time when the driver's licence was drawn up, marital status, type of car to be insured and its use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
Because it is even harder to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, it must be clear what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and a policyholder.
This agreement is recorded in writing by means of an insurance contract which states that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to present the corresponding severance sum in case of damage.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance which is composed of several factors, including age, sex, time of drawing up the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or its use.
Insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contributions are also due in the event of a higher risk of accidents.
For this reason, both 25-year-olds and women have to pay less, as statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, who, according to the statistical values and therefore also to the firm's conviction, tend to have fewer accidents than single persons.
The benefits attributed to the vehicle affect the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
In drawing up the premium, insurance companies must take account of a number of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best suits his personal needs.
We now list the most important points that should be considered when choosing an insurance policy in order to be able to make not only a performance but also a price-oriented choice.
The under-25s encounter numerous obstacles when choosing low-cost insurance, such as low driving practice and a young driver's license.
Even if it would be best to take out comprehensive insurance for an ideal insurance cover, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The careful drivers can choose a fully self-sufficient, so that the benefits of a fully comprehensive insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer must pay part of the amount incurred as a result of the damage himself.
The amount is determined before the conclusion of the contract and based on the amount of the insurance premium, which is higher the lower the amount to be paid, explains Luis Noguera, the main representative of Spain at First Europa, an online insurance broker.
Another option is extended insurance, which insures the customer against external accident damage, but not against the damage caused to his own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here's some advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is in your hands to reduce insurance costs; so your credit increases by trying to drive carefully and avoid accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate of the corresponding insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment involves an increase in the tariff in question.
The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its income.
If the company has a profitable year behind it, it may allow itself to increase the bonus payments, explains Noguera.
As soon as the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for the drivers to conclude a contract. This is due to the fact that the accident rate decreases with increasing driving practice.
Thus, it makes the most sense to opt for a comprehensive insurance with excess.
Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving, explains the Spanish manager of the European company, and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the fear of the beginner has been abandoned.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out comprehensive insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the corresponding person allows it.
The insurers consider married couples with children to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and accordingly their contributions are also low.
In this case, the best option would be a fully comprehensive insurance with a deductible (for an amount of around 300 euros). In the event that you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy is recommended, which will only start for the third year of the vehicle.
They drive more relaxed overall and have a greater purchasing power, which allows them to set up a higher contribution payment, Luis Noguera notes.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out a comprehensive insurance with a deductible (for an amount of around 150 euros) or an extended insurance, which only applies with a sufficiently high credit.
In the end, it is important to note that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accident damage, but also because it involves high costs, which require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
